page.title: 02INTRODUCTION:continued
page.content:
The village of Flushing has always been associated with the sea. For many years the locals have fished the surrounding seas and have recently formed a fishing co-operative to make the fishing and marketing more efficient.
The natural harbour of Falmouth has been a major port of call for ships from all over the world since Tudor times. The packet service ran from Falmouth for much of the 18th and 19th century and news of many famous battles first arrived at Falmouth. Most of the Packet captains and their crews lived in Flushing and the Packet captains' houses are part of the Georgian sea frontage today.
